# Weather App - South Africa

This project is a simple weather application that displays weather information for various cities in South Africa. The app consists of a frontend (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) that interacts with a backend API (Node.js and Express) to fetch weather data.

## Features

- Display current weather and future forecasts for cities in South Africa.
- Change the city to get weather updates for different locations.
- Backend API serves weather data for predefined cities.
- User-friendly interface with responsive design.

## Project Structure

- `index.html` - The main frontend page that displays weather information.
- `style.css` - CSS styles for the frontend.
- `server.js` - Node.js backend that provides weather data for different cities.
- `package.json` - Contains project dependencies and metadata.

##To Getting Started

Follow the steps below to run this project locally on your machine.

### Prerequisites

Before you begin, make sure you have the following installed:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en/download/) (version 12.x or later)
- [Git](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git)

### Clone the Repository

1. Open your terminal or command prompt.
2. Clone the repository using the following command:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/weather-app.git
